(2, 0, 'Can Honey Really Help You Lose Weight? Here’s the Truth', '<p> Yes...Honey has about 64 calories and 17g of sugar per tablespoon — slightly more calories than white sugar by weight.</p>\\r\\n<p>It contains trace amounts of antioxidants, vitamins, and minerals, unlike refined sugar.</p>\\r\\n<p>If you’re replacing refined sugar or artificial sweet with a small amount of honey, you may consume ultra-processed foods.</p>\\r\\n<p>Infect you can replace sugar in tea, coffee, or oatmeal with <strong data-start=\\\"1531\\\" data-end=\\\"1554\\\">½ teaspoon of honey</strong> instead of large amounts of sugar.</p>\\r\\n<p><strong data-start=\\\"223\\\" data-end=\\\"263\\\">Science Behind Honey for Weight Loss</strong></p>\\r\\n<p><strong data-start=\\\"223\\\" data-end=\\\"263\\\">Honey Regulates Blood Sugar Better Than Sugar</strong></p>\\r\\n<p><strong data-start=\\\"223\\\" data-end=\\\"263\\\">Sugar spikes → insulin increases → body stores more fat.</strong></p>\\r\\n<p><strong data-start=\\\"223\\\" data-end=\\\"263\\\">Honey releases glucose slowly, preventing sudden insulin spikes.<br data-start=\\\"537\\\" data-end=\\\"540\\\">✔ Stable blood sugar<br data-start=\\\"560\\\" data-end=\\\"563\\\">✔ Less fat storage<br data-start=\\\"581\\\" data-end=\\\"584\\\">✔ Reduced cravings</strong></p>\\r\\n<p><strong data-start=\\\"223\\\" data-end=\\\"263\\\">It also Acts as a natural cough suppressant and throat soother (often used with warm water or turmeric).</strong></p>\\r\\n<p><strong data-start=\\\"223\\\" data-end=\\\"263\\\">Promotes melatonin release, helping with better sleep quality.</strong></p>\\r\\n<p> </p>', 'uploads/media/2025/rsz_1h_for_b.jpg', 'can-honey-really-help-you-lose-weight-heres-the-truth', 1, '2025-09-29 12:45:41'),
(4, 5, 'Empowering Rural Women: The Backbone of New India', '<p>Empowering rural women is crucial for sustainable development, poverty reduction, and the overall well-being of communities. Rural women often face systemic challenges like limited access to education, healthcare, credit, land ownership, and decision-making power.</p>\\r\\n<p>Rural women make up <strong data-start=\\\"325\\\" data-end=\\\"367\\\">over 70% of the agricultural workforce</strong> in India.</p>\\r\\n<p>They contribute heavily to <strong data-start=\\\"407\\\" data-end=\\\"453\\\">farming, animal husbandry, food processing</strong>, and <strong data-start=\\\"459\\\" data-end=\\\"474\\\">handicrafts</strong>, yet often remain <strong data-start=\\\"493\\\" data-end=\\\"516\\\">unpaid or underpaid</strong>.</p>\\r\\n<p>When rural women earn, they invest more in their families and communities.</p>\\r\\n<h2 data-start=\\\"631\\\" data-end=\\\"684\\\"><strong data-start=\\\"637\\\" data-end=\\\"682\\\"> They Are the Backbone of Rural Economy</strong></h2>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"685\\\" data-end=\\\"788\\\">Rural women work in:<br data-start=\\\"705\\\" data-end=\\\"708\\\">✔ Agriculture<br data-start=\\\"721\\\" data-end=\\\"724\\\">✔ Livestock<br data-start=\\\"735\\\" data-end=\\\"738\\\">✔ Dairy<br data-start=\\\"745\\\" data-end=\\\"748\\\">✔ Handicrafts<br data-start=\\\"761\\\" data-end=\\\"764\\\">✔ Household production</p>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"790\\\" data-end=\\\"915\\\"><em><strong>Yet their contribution is undervalued.</strong></em><br data-start=\\\"828\\\" data-end=\\\"831\\\">Empowering them increases village income, productivity, and overall economic growth.</p>', 'uploads/media/2025/dang_woman_working1.jpg', 'empowering-rural-women-the-backbone-of-new-india', 1, '2025-09-29 13:14:31'),
(5, 7, 'Lakadong Haldi: The Golden Super-Spice of India', '<p>It’s called <strong>Lakadong haldi</strong> because it comes from a specific place named <strong data-start=\\\"76\\\" data-end=\\\"96\\\">Lakadong village</strong>, in the <strong data-start=\\\"105\\\" data-end=\\\"143\\\">Jaintia Hills of Meghalaya (India)</strong>.</p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n<li data-start=\\\"306\\\" data-end=\\\"354\\\">\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"308\\\" data-end=\\\"354\\\">Normal turmeric has about <strong data-start=\\\"334\\\" data-end=\\\"351\\\">2–4% curcumin</strong>.</p>\\r\\n</li>\\r\\n<li data-start=\\\"358\\\" data-end=\\\"428\\\">\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"360\\\" data-end=\\\"428\\\">Lakadong haldi has <strong data-start=\\\"379\\\" data-end=\\\"397\\\">7–12% curcumin</strong>, making it much more potent.</p>\\r\\n</li>\\r\\n<li data-start=\\\"657\\\" data-end=\\\"723\\\">\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"659\\\" data-end=\\\"723\\\">Strong <strong data-start=\\\"666\\\" data-end=\\\"687\\\">anti-inflammatory</strong> (good for arthritis, joint pain).</p>\\r\\n</li>\\r\\n<li data-start=\\\"727\\\" data-end=\\\"798\\\">\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"729\\\" data-end=\\\"798\\\">Powerful <strong data-start=\\\"738\\\" data-end=\\\"753\\\">antioxidant</strong> (fights free radicals, supports immunity).</p>\\r\\n</li>\\r\\n<li data-start=\\\"802\\\" data-end=\\\"842\\\">\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"804\\\" data-end=\\\"842\\\">Supports <strong data-start=\\\"813\\\" data-end=\\\"839\\\">digestion & gut health</strong>.</p>\\r\\n</li>\\r\\n<li data-start=\\\"846\\\" data-end=\\\"887\\\">\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"848\\\" data-end=\\\"887\\\">Promotes <strong data-start=\\\"857\\\" data-end=\\\"884\\\">skin health and healing</strong>.</p>\\r\\n</li>\\r\\n<li data-start=\\\"916\\\" data-end=\\\"952\\\">\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"918\\\" data-end=\\\"952\\\">Usually grown without chemicals.</p>\\r\\n</li>\\r\\n<li data-start=\\\"956\\\" data-end=\\\"1008\\\">\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"958\\\" data-end=\\\"1008\\\">Bright, deep yellow color (because of curcumin).</p>\\r\\n</li>\\r\\n<li data-start=\\\"956\\\" data-end=\\\"1008\\\">Powerful Anti-Inflammatory Properties</li>\\r\\n<li data-start=\\\"956\\\" data-end=\\\"1008\\\">So its helpfull in</li>\\r\\n<li data-start=\\\"956\\\" data-end=\\\"1008\\\">Joint pain<br data-start=\\\"1321\\\" data-end=\\\"1324\\\">✔ Joint pain<br data-start=\\\"1321\\\" data-end=\\\"1324\\\">✔ Swelling<br data-start=\\\"1334\\\" data-end=\\\"1337\\\">✔ Arthritis symptoms<br data-start=\\\"1357\\\" data-end=\\\"1360\\\">✔ Muscle stiffness</li>\\r\\n<li data-start=\\\"956\\\" data-end=\\\"1008\\\"> </li>\\r\\n<li data-start=\\\"956\\\" data-end=\\\"1008\\\"><em><strong>How to use Lakadong Haldi daily?</strong></em></li>\\r\\n<li data-start=\\\"956\\\" data-end=\\\"1008\\\"> </li>\\r\\n</ul>\\r\\n<h3 data-start=\\\"2106\\\" data-end=\\\"2140\\\"><strong data-start=\\\"2112\\\" data-end=\\\"2138\\\">1. Morning Haldi Water</strong></h3>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"2141\\\" data-end=\\\"2183\\\">½ tsp Lakadong haldi + warm water + honey.</p>\\r\\n<h3 data-start=\\\"2185\\\" data-end=\\\"2225\\\"><strong data-start=\\\"2191\\\" data-end=\\\"2223\\\">2. Golden Milk (Haldi Doodh)</strong></h3>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"2226\\\" data-end=\\\"2255\\\">Perfect for immunity & sleep.</p>\\r\\n<h3 data-start=\\\"2257\\\" data-end=\\\"2285\\\"><strong data-start=\\\"2263\\\" data-end=\\\"2283\\\">3. Daily Cooking</strong></h3>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"2286\\\" data-end=\\\"2320\\\">Add to curries, dal, sabzi, soups.</p>\\r\\n<h3 data-start=\\\"2322\\\" data-end=\\\"2357\\\"><strong data-start=\\\"2328\\\" data-end=\\\"2355\\\">4. Detox Drinks & Kadha</strong></h3>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"2358\\\" data-end=\\\"2398\\\">Boosts digestion & reduces inflammation.</p>\\r\\n<h3 data-start=\\\"2400\\\" data-end=\\\"2436\\\"><strong data-start=\\\"2406\\\" data-end=\\\"2434\\\">5. Face Packs (Optional)</strong></h3>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"2437\\\" data-end=\\\"2477\\\">Mix with curd, rose water, or aloevera</p>', 'uploads/media/2025/SEOon_TURMERIC-Slides-V3_2-1-1_(6).jpg', 'lakadong-haldi-the-golden-super-spice-of-india', 1, '2025-09-30 05:59:38'),
(6, 8, 'Why jaggery in routin life', '<p>Jaggery (called <strong>“gud ”</strong> in Hindi) is a natural sweetener made from sugarcane juice or palm sap. Unlike refined sugar, it retains minerals and nutrients, which makes it a healthier option.</p>\\r\\n<p> <strong>JAGGERY</strong> is very rich in minrals as it contains iron, magnesium, potassium, and phosphorus that support overall health.</p>\\r\\n<p>Acts as a natural cleanser for the digestive system and prevents constipation by active digestive enzymes.</p>\\r\\n<p>Provides slow-releasing energy (unlike sugar spikes), keeping you energetic longer.</p>\\r\\n<p>Traditionally used to ease cough, cold, asthma, and bronchial problems when combined with black sesame or ginger.</p>\\r\\n<p>Its antioxidants and minerals help the body fight infections.</p>\\r\\n<p>Even in fitness routin athletes and gym-goers use jaggery for quick recovery and natural energy instead of artificial supplements.</p>\\r\\n<p>Consuming jaggery with sesame or peanuts in winter improves bone strength: with water in summer, it cools and refreshes the body.</p>\\r\\n<p>REPLACE WHITE SUGAR WITH JAGGERY</p>\\r\\n<p>Use jaggery in:<br data-start=\\\"506\\\" data-end=\\\"509\\\">• Tea<br data-start=\\\"514\\\" data-end=\\\"517\\\">• Coffee (optional)<br data-start=\\\"536\\\" data-end=\\\"539\\\">• Milk<br data-start=\\\"545\\\" data-end=\\\"548\\\">• Breakfast porridge<br data-start=\\\"568\\\" data-end=\\\"571\\\">• Desserts<br data-start=\\\"581\\\" data-end=\\\"584\\\">• Kheer / Halwa</p>\\r\\n<p>Eat a small piece of it after lunch</p>\\r\\n<p>You can also use jaggery to your chapati or rotla</p>\\r\\n<p>Best in herbal drinks like ginger tea, tulsi tea ,khawa etc...</p>', 'uploads/media/2025/jaggery-powder_(2).jpg', 'why-jaggery-in-routin-life', 1, '2025-09-30 07:06:05'),
(7, 9, 'Moringa powder for morden life', '<p>Moringa powder, made from the dry leaves of the Moringa oleifera tree (also called the \\\"drumstick tree\\\" or \\\"miracle tree\\\"), is often called a <strong>superfood</strong> because of its dense nutrition and medical properties.</p>\\r\\n<p>Its very rich in nutrients as it contains vitamins A, C, E, K, and B-complex, plus calcium, potassium, magnesium, iron, and protein.</p>\\r\\n<p>Strengthens defense against infections, pollution, and lifestyle-related illnesses.</p>\\r\\n<p>Provides natural energy without caffeine—useful for busy, modern routines.</p>\\r\\n<p>Vitamin A, C, and E nourish skin, fight acne, delay aging signs, and strengthen hair roots.</p>\\r\\n<p>Helps relieve joint pain, arthritis, and inflammation caused by sedentary lifestyle.</p>\\r\\n<p>High calcium and vitamin A content keep bones strong and improve eyesight.</p>\\r\\n<p>Moringa powder also supports in weight loss and controls your blood sugar levels.</p>\\r\\n<p><em><strong>HOW TO USE MORINGA POWDER IN YOUR DAILY USE?</strong></em></p>\\r\\n<h3 data-start=\\\"2413\\\" data-end=\\\"2447\\\"><strong data-start=\\\"2419\\\" data-end=\\\"2445\\\">1.Morning detox drink </strong></h3>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"2448\\\" data-end=\\\"2490\\\">Mix 1 tsp moringa in warm water + lemon.</p>\\r\\n<h3 data-start=\\\"2492\\\" data-end=\\\"2532\\\"><strong data-start=\\\"2498\\\" data-end=\\\"2530\\\">2. Add in Smoothies & Juices</strong></h3>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"2533\\\" data-end=\\\"2564\\\">Enhances nutrition instantly.</p>\\r\\n<h3 data-start=\\\"2566\\\" data-end=\\\"2597\\\"><strong data-start=\\\"2572\\\" data-end=\\\"2595\\\">3. Sprinkle on Food</strong></h3>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"2598\\\" data-end=\\\"2637\\\">Use over salads, dal, sabzi, khichdi.</p>\\r\\n<h3 data-start=\\\"2639\\\" data-end=\\\"2666\\\"><strong data-start=\\\"2645\\\" data-end=\\\"2664\\\">4. Mix in Dough</strong></h3>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"2667\\\" data-end=\\\"2721\\\">Add moringa powder in wheat flour for healthy roti.</p>\\r\\n<h3 data-start=\\\"2723\\\" data-end=\\\"2757\\\"><strong data-start=\\\"2729\\\" data-end=\\\"2755\\\">5. Add to Tea or Kadha</strong></h3>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"2758\\\" data-end=\\\"2777\\\">Boost immune power.</p>\\r\\n<h3 data-start=\\\"2779\\\" data-end=\\\"2829\\\"><strong data-start=\\\"2785\\\" data-end=\\\"2827\\\">6. Make Healthy Ladoos or Energy Bites</strong></h3>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"2830\\\" data-end=\\\"2856\\\">Great for kids and elders.</p>', 'uploads/media/2025/mo3_(1).jpg', 'moringa-powder-for-morden-life', 1, '2025-09-30 11:26:00'),
(8, 12, '“Millets: The Ancient Superfood Making a Modern Comeback”', '<p>A balanced diet by millets is a dietary pattern in which various millets such as</p>\\r\\n<p>Ragi (finger millet), jowar (sorghum), bajra (pearl millet), foxtail millet, little millet, barnyard millet, and kodo millet are incorporated in appropriate amounts to meet the body’s nutritional requirements, maintain energy, support growth, and prevent lifestyle-related diseases.</p>\\r\\n<p>Improves digestion and controls weight</p>\\r\\n<p>Supports muscles and tissue repair.</p>\\r\\n<p><strong>Loaded with minerals</strong> like calcium (ragi), iron (bajra), magnesium, zinc.</p>\\r\\n<p>suitable for people with gluten intolerance.</p>\\r\\n<p>combining different millets ensures balance in nutrients.</p>\\r\\n<p>Millets are very usefull at controlling diabites.</p>\\r\\n<p>Also boots heart health.</p>\\r\\n<h1 data-start=\\\"2654\\\" data-end=\\\"2699\\\"><strong data-start=\\\"2658\\\" data-end=\\\"2699\\\">How to Add Millets to Your Daily Diet</strong></h1>\\r\\n<h3 data-start=\\\"2701\\\" data-end=\\\"2723\\\">➤ Millet khichdi</h3>\\r\\n<h3 data-start=\\\"2724\\\" data-end=\\\"2751\\\">➤ Millet upma or poha</h3>\\r\\n<h3 data-start=\\\"2752\\\" data-end=\\\"2777\\\">➤ Ragi rotla / roti</h3>\\r\\n<h3 data-start=\\\"2778\\\" data-end=\\\"2804\\\">➤ Millet dosa / idli</h3>\\r\\n<h3 data-start=\\\"2805\\\" data-end=\\\"2836\\\">➤ Millet ladoo for kids</h3>\\r\\n<h3 data-start=\\\"2837\\\" data-end=\\\"2880\\\">➤ Millet flour mixed with wheat flour</h3>', 'uploads/media/2025/mil2_(1).jpg', 'millets-the-ancient-superfood-making-a-modern-comeback', 1, '2025-10-02 06:33:20'),
(9, 10, 'Skin care boots your confidence', '<p>A proper routine can reduce acne, dryness, pigmentation, and other common issues.</p>\\r\\n<p>It slows aging as Regular care with cleansing, moisturizing, and sun protection helps delay wrinkles and fine lines.</p>\\r\\n<p>Skin care shields your skin from harmful UV rays, dirt, and toxins.</p>\\r\\n<p>Your skin is the body’s first defense barrier; keeping it clean and nourished maintains its protective function.</p>\\r\\n<p><strong>In short Skin care is not just about beauty, it’s about health, protection, and confidence.</strong></p>', 'uploads/media/2025/skin_care1.jpg', 'skin-care-boots-your-confidence', 0, '2025-10-03 07:54:55'),
(16, 11, 'Cold- pressed purity, rich in nutrition', '<p>Rich in Monounsaturated & polyunsaturated fats that help maintain cholesterol levels and support heart health,</p>\\r\\n<p>so its heart friendly oil.</p>\\r\\n<p>Contains Vitamin E which protects cells from damage and boosts immunity.</p>\\r\\n<p>Traditional goodness as Ideal for Indian cooking, frying, and everyday use with authentic taste.</p>\\r\\n<p>Good to digest as Its natural composition makes food lighter to compared to refined oils.</p>\\r\\n<p>Vitamin E and natural nutrients help keep skin soft and hair strong.</p>\\r\\n<p>Its natural and chemical free. So no bleaching, no refining, no preservatives. This means you get <strong data-start=\\\"361\\\" data-end=\\\"386\\\">pure, clean, safe oil</strong> every day.</p>\\r\\n<p><em><strong>Perfect for Daily Cooking</strong></em></p>\\r\\n<p>As you can use it in Sabzi, Dal tadka, Rotis, Salads, Frying / sauteing </p>\\r\\n<h1 data-start=\\\"1418\\\" data-end=\\\"1443\\\"><strong data-start=\\\"1423\\\" data-end=\\\"1441\\\">Final Thought:</strong></h1>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"1444\\\" data-end=\\\"1604\\\">Using cold-pressed oil daily is one of the <strong data-start=\\\"1487\\\" data-end=\\\"1532\\\">simplest and healthiest lifestyle changes</strong> you can make — for your heart, skin, digestion, and overall well-being.</p>', 'uploads/media/2025/copre1.jpg', 'cold-pressed-purity-rich-in-nutrition', 1, '2025-10-03 12:56:48'),
(17, 13, 'Bilona A2 Cow Ghee: The Ancient Method That Makes All the Difference', '<p>The <strong data-start=\\\"236\\\" data-end=\\\"253\\\">Bilona Method</strong> is an <strong data-start=\\\"260\\\" data-end=\\\"287\\\">ancient Vedic technique</strong> of making <strong data-start=\\\"298\\\" data-end=\\\"313\\\">A2 cow Ghee</strong> in the purest and most traditional way.<br data-start=\\\"353\\\" data-end=\\\"356\\\">Instead of machines, chemicals, or high heat — the Bilona process uses <strong data-start=\\\"427\\\" data-end=\\\"444\\\">hand-churning</strong>, <strong data-start=\\\"446\\\" data-end=\\\"462\\\">earthen pots</strong>, and <strong data-start=\\\"468\\\" data-end=\\\"484\\\">slow cooking</strong>, just like our ancestors did.</p>\\r\\n<h1 data-start=\\\"521\\\" data-end=\\\"570\\\"><strong data-start=\\\"525\\\" data-end=\\\"570\\\">Step-by-Step — How Bilona A2 Ghee Is Made</strong></h1>\\r\\n<h2 data-start=\\\"577\\\" data-end=\\\"625\\\"><strong data-start=\\\"583\\\" data-end=\\\"623\\\">1. Start with A2 Milk from Desi Cows</strong></h2>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"626\\\" data-end=\\\"825\\\">The process begins with <strong data-start=\\\"650\\\" data-end=\\\"661\\\">A2 milk</strong>, which comes from Indian desi cow breeds (Gir, Sahiwal, Rathi, Kankrej, etc.).<br data-start=\\\"740\\\" data-end=\\\"743\\\">This milk contains the <strong data-start=\\\"766\\\" data-end=\\\"780\\\">A2 protein</strong>, known to be easier to digest and healthier.</p>\\r\\n<h2 data-start=\\\"832\\\" data-end=\\\"886\\\"><strong data-start=\\\"838\\\" data-end=\\\"884\\\">2. Milk Is Boiled and Set into Curd (Dahi)</strong></h2>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"887\\\" data-end=\\\"1002\\\">The milk is boiled, cooled, and made into <strong data-start=\\\"929\\\" data-end=\\\"937\\\">curd</strong> using a natural culture.<br data-start=\\\"962\\\" data-end=\\\"965\\\">✔ No chemicals<br data-start=\\\"979\\\" data-end=\\\"982\\\">✔ No preservatives</p>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"1004\\\" data-end=\\\"1039\\\">This curd is left to set overnight.</p>\\r\\n<h2 data-start=\\\"1046\\\" data-end=\\\"1105\\\"><strong data-start=\\\"1052\\\" data-end=\\\"1103\\\">3. Curd Is Hand-Churned (Bilona) to Make Makhan</strong></h2>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"1106\\\" data-end=\\\"1238\\\">This is the heart of the process.<br data-start=\\\"1139\\\" data-end=\\\"1142\\\">The curd is put in a <strong data-start=\\\"1163\\\" data-end=\\\"1180\\\">wooden vessel</strong> and churned using a <strong data-start=\\\"1201\\\" data-end=\\\"1219\\\">wooden churner</strong> (called <em data-start=\\\"1228\\\" data-end=\\\"1236\\\">bilona</em>).</p>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"1240\\\" data-end=\\\"1314\\\">Churning is done:<br data-start=\\\"1257\\\" data-end=\\\"1260\\\">✔ Clockwise<br data-start=\\\"1271\\\" data-end=\\\"1274\\\">✔ Anti-clockwise<br data-start=\\\"1290\\\" data-end=\\\"1293\\\">✔ Slowly, for hours</p>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"1316\\\" data-end=\\\"1333\\\">This separates:</p>\\r\\n<ul data-start=\\\"1334\\\" data-end=\\\"1384\\\">\\r\\n<li data-start=\\\"1334\\\" data-end=\\\"1357\\\">\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"1336\\\" data-end=\\\"1357\\\"><strong data-start=\\\"1336\\\" data-end=\\\"1355\\\">Makhan (butter)</strong></p>\\r\\n</li>\\r\\n<li data-start=\\\"1358\\\" data-end=\\\"1384\\\">\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"1360\\\" data-end=\\\"1384\\\"><strong data-start=\\\"1360\\\" data-end=\\\"1382\\\">Matha (buttermilk)</strong></p>\\r\\n<h2 data-start=\\\"1444\\\" data-end=\\\"1502\\\"><strong data-start=\\\"1450\\\" data-end=\\\"1500\\\">4. Makhan Is Collected and Heated on Low Flame</strong></h2>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"1503\\\" data-end=\\\"1604\\\">The makhan is taken out and melted on a <strong data-start=\\\"1543\\\" data-end=\\\"1556\\\">low flame</strong>, usually in an <strong data-start=\\\"1572\\\" data-end=\\\"1587\\\">earthen pot</strong> or steel vessel.</p>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"1606\\\" data-end=\\\"1697\\\">Slow heating ensures:<br data-start=\\\"1627\\\" data-end=\\\"1630\\\">✔ Nutrients stay intact<br data-start=\\\"1653\\\" data-end=\\\"1656\\\">✔ No burning<br data-start=\\\"1668\\\" data-end=\\\"1671\\\">✔ Pure golden ghee aroma</p>\\r\\n<h2 data-start=\\\"1704\\\" data-end=\\\"1747\\\"><strong data-start=\\\"1710\\\" data-end=\\\"1745\\\">5. The Pure A2 Ghee Is Filtered</strong></h2>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"1748\\\" data-end=\\\"1880\\\">When the makhan releases its natural aroma and turns golden, it becomes <strong data-start=\\\"1820\\\" data-end=\\\"1838\\\">A2 Bilona Ghee</strong>.<br data-start=\\\"1839\\\" data-end=\\\"1842\\\">It is then gently filtered and stored.</p>\\r\\n</li>\\r\\n</ul>', 'uploads/media/2025/ghee3_(1).jpg', 'bilona-a2-cow-ghee-the-ancient-method-that-makes-all-the-difference', 1, '2025-11-15 12:53:54'),
(18, 0, 'Organic Living: Why Choosing Natural Products Is a Gift to Your Family', '<p>In today’s fast-moving world, we try our best to give our families the safest, healthiest, and happiest life. But sometimes, the simplest choices make the biggest difference—like choosing what we put on our skin, what we eat, and what we use in our homes.<br data-start=\\\"400\\\" data-end=\\\"403\\\">This is where <strong data-start=\\\"417\\\" data-end=\\\"435\\\">organic living</strong> becomes more than just a trend.<br data-start=\\\"467\\\" data-end=\\\"470\\\">It becomes a <em data-start=\\\"483\\\" data-end=\\\"489\\\">gift</em>—a gift of purity, protection, and love.</p>\\r\\n<h2 data-start=\\\"536\\\" data-end=\\\"590\\\">❤️ <strong data-start=\\\"542\\\" data-end=\\\"590\\\">Because Your Family Deserves the Purest Care</strong></h2>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"592\\\" data-end=\\\"704\\\">Every parent, every homemaker, every caring heart always wants one thing:<br data-start=\\\"665\\\" data-end=\\\"668\\\"><strong data-start=\\\"668\\\" data-end=\\\"704\\\">to protect the people they love.</strong></p>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"706\\\" data-end=\\\"925\\\">But modern products often contain chemicals, artificial preservatives, and synthetic additives that we don’t even notice. Over time, these can silently affect our skin, our immunity, and even our emotional health.</p>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"927\\\" data-end=\\\"1085\\\"><strong data-start=\\\"927\\\" data-end=\\\"1003\\\">Choosing natural and organic products is like choosing a safe tomorrow.</strong><br data-start=\\\"1003\\\" data-end=\\\"1006\\\">They are gentle, cleaner, and crafted with ingredients trusted by generations.</p>', 'uploads/media/2025/o_l.png', 'organic-living-why-choosing-natural-products-is-a-gift-to-your-family', 1, '2025-11-17 06:06:59'),
(19, 0, 'Why Handmade Products Carry More Love Than Factory-Made Items', '<p>In a world where machines create thousands of identical products every minute, handmade items stand apart like a warm heartbeat in a room full of noise. Every handmade product carries a story—a story of the person who shaped it, the time they invested, and the emotion they poured into it. When an artisan crafts something by hand, they are not just producing an item; they are sharing a part of their soul, their culture, and their creativity. Unlike factory-made products that move along fast conveyor belts, handmade goods grow slowly, with attention to detail in every step.</p>\\r\\n<h3 data-start=\\\"523\\\" data-end=\\\"557\\\"><strong data-start=\\\"530\\\" data-end=\\\"555\\\">Every Piece Is Unique</strong></h3>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"558\\\" data-end=\\\"843\\\">Unlike factory-made items that are produced in bulk, every handmade product is one-of-a-kind. Slight imperfection  or variations aren’t flaws; they’re the mark of authenticity, a testament to the maker’s hands and heart. Owning a handmade item means owning something truly exclusive.</p>\\r\\n<h3 data-start=\\\"845\\\" data-end=\\\"875\\\"><strong data-start=\\\"852\\\" data-end=\\\"873\\\">Crafted With Care</strong></h3>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"876\\\" data-end=\\\"1170\\\">Artisans invest time, effort, and passion into their creations. Every stitch, brushstroke, or carve is done with intention. This meticulous attention to detail ensures a quality that mass-produced items often lack. When you buy handmade, you’re supporting the labour of love that went into it.</p>\\r\\n<h3 data-start=\\\"1512\\\" data-end=\\\"1549\\\"><strong data-start=\\\"1519\\\" data-end=\\\"1547\\\">Environmentally Friendly</strong></h3>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"1550\\\" data-end=\\\"1846\\\">Handmade products generally have a smaller carbon footprint. They are often made with sustainable materials and processes, unlike factory-made items, which can involve heavy machinery, chemical processing, and long transportation chains. Choosing handmade is a step toward eco-conscious living.</p>\\r\\n<h3 data-start=\\\"1848\\\" data-end=\\\"1881\\\"><strong data-start=\\\"1855\\\" data-end=\\\"1879\\\">Emotional Connection</strong></h3>\\r\\n<p data-start=\\\"1882\\\" data-end=\\\"2164\\\">There’s an emotional resonance in knowing that a human, not a machine, crafted your item. Handmade products often feel warmer, more personal, and more meaningful. They’re not just objects; they’re stories, memories, and expressions of human creativity that you can touch and feel.</p>', 'uploads/media/2025/handmade-vs-machine-code.png', 'why-handmade-products-carry-more-love-than-factory-made-items', 1, '2025-11-17 07:10:04');
